File: Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC, Panyaza Lesufi has apologised for mistakenly spotting the old South African flag at the Springboks' semifinal victory. Lesufi on Sunday posted a picture of Springboks supporters in Japan carrying what seemed to him like the old flag. He captioned the picture as a spoiler. WATCH: Gratuitous display of Apartheid flag hate speech Twitter users were quick to correct Lesufi and he's apologised. Lesufi says his reaction was prompted by the trauma of apartheid.